sentences: Monica Huggett (born 16 May 1953 in London, England) is a British conductor and leading baroque violinist.
She co-founded and served as leader of the Amsterdam Baroque Orchestra under Ton Koopman from 1980 to 1987.
She was made a Fellow of the Royal Academy of Music in 1994, and serves as professor of baroque violin at the Hochschule für Künste Bremen, Germany.
She has won Gramophone Awards for her recordings of Bach's Sonatas and Partitas for solo violin (1997) and Biber's violin sonatas (2002).
She has won Gramophone Awards for her recordings of Bach's Sonatas and Partitas for solo violin (1997) and Biber's violin sonatas (2002).
In 2008 she was appointed director of the new graduate program in historical performance at The Juilliard School in New York City.
